ch.ecma.csta.binding

Class GetPhysicalDeviceInformationResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • ch.ecma.csta.binding.GetPhysicalDeviceInformationResponse
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class GetPhysicalDeviceInformationResponse
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    The GetPhysicalDeviceInformationResponse has these parameters.

    GetPhysicalDeviceInformationResponse Supported Parameters
    deviceCategory Mandatory Specifies the device category (station, ACD device, etc.) of the device being queried. The supported values are: group, station(default) and other.
    groupDeviceAttributes Conditional Specifies the group device attributes of the device being queried. If a bit is TRUE then the specified attribute is present. The following attributes are supported: Hunt and Acd.
    hasLogicalElement Optional Specifies if the device has a logical element associated with this device identifier. The complete set of possible values is: FALSE - The device does not have a logical element. TRUE - The device does have a logical element
    otherLogicalDeviceList Optional Specifies the list of device identifiers for other devices with logical elements that are associated with this device.
    Version:
    $Revision$ $Date$
